The paper deals with biomedical segmentation using CNN-based volumetric methods and proposes a two-stream encoder/decoder architecture that simultaneously performs segmentation and recovers a 3D mesh. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves mesh modeling, which falls under the Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. The use of deep learning techniques for segmentation and mesh modeling also suggests that the paper could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with biomedical data, which could place it under the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
